        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimation. This value does not reflect real conditions. The annual production volume determines the shares of supplying activities on a certain market. 
The share of heat, central or small-scale, natural gas from CHP plants was assumed to amount to 5%; the share from pure heat plants was assumed to amount to 95%. The annual production volumes of all supplying datasets reflect these shares on the market, but are not realistic production volumes. 

See talk pages for further discussion of the modelling of the heat markets.</productionVolumeComment>
